CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer vmalloc(sizeof(*midi_in_buf[dev])...) over vmalloc(sizeof(struct midi_buf)...)
#77: FILE: sound/oss/midibuf.c:180:
+	midi_in_buf[dev] = vmalloc(sizeof(struct midi_buf));

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer vmalloc(sizeof(*midi_out_buf[dev])...) over vmalloc(sizeof(struct midi_buf)...)
#86: FILE: sound/oss/midibuf.c:190:
+	midi_out_buf[dev] = vmalloc(sizeof(struct midi_buf));

ERROR:POINTER_LOCATION: "(foo*)" should be "(foo *)"
#177: FILE: sound/pci/emu10k1/emu10k1_main.c:1249:
+	emu->page_ptr_table = vmalloc(emu->max_cache_pages * sizeof(void*));

When using pointer data or a function that returns a pointer type,
the preferred use of * is adjacent to the data name or function name
and not adjacent to the type name.
Examples::

  char *linux_banner;
  unsigned long long memparse(char *ptr, char **retptr);
  char *match_strdup(substring_t *s);

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

